Description: Ostracon, fragment of the body of a drab-coloured pottery vessel, the fabric is grey in section, the exterior is covered with a cream-coloured slip, now very discoloured, and faint traces of two lines of black-painted hieratic text.
Bibliographic references: Trismegistos / An interdisciplinary portal of papyrological and epigraphic resources (394018) (http://www.trismegistos.org/text/394018)
